parameters:
Chieftain: "Ho, so you're the young man who washed up in our village... You
fell from the waterfall and survived, I hear?"

Krun: "Yes, I'm in your debt. Thanks to Umi and Mi-A, I was able to cling
to life."

Chieftain: "Is that so, is that so. You've been asleep for a whole month,
so your body must be quite stiff, I'd wager."
Krun: "A month!? "
Chieftain: "What's with the loud voice?"
Umi: "You're being noisy."

Krun: "I apologize, I lost my composure. Have I really been asleep that
long?"

Chieftain: "Well, you did fall from a waterfall, so it's only natural it
took that long to recover. Had you slept for another week, we might have
ended up roasting and eating you."
Umi: "Too bad."
Krun: "What!!!"

Chieftain: "Ho ho ho. Just a chieftain's joke, lad. We don't eat people
here."
Umi: "Idiot."
Krun: "Phew, that's a relief. Of course, you were joking... right?"
Chieftain: "Now, onto the main issue. Do you know where you are?"

Krun: "No, not at all. I was searching for the people of the Holy Child's
Forest, but I don't even know if this is within the Holy Child's Forest."

Chieftain: "This is indeed within the Holy Child's Forest. And the people
you're looking for are us."
Krun: "What! What a coincidence!"

Chieftain: "Ho ho ho, there are no coincidences. You were guided here by
our god, Kusechirei-sama. Otherwise, you would never have found our
village."

Krun: "I see. So there must be some sort of barrier or something over this
forest."

Chieftain: "Ho ho ho. Kusechirei-sama is great indeed. Now, why were you
looking for us?"

Krun: "Yes. The lord commanded me to find the altar of the god enshrined in
this forest. That's why I was exploring these woods."

Chieftain: "I see. That's something we can't exactly welcome, but the fact
that you made it here with that intent suggests that it was Kusechirei-
sama's guidance as well."
Banka: "I'm interrupting!"
Banka: "Hey old man! Is this guy the intruder we were talking about?"
Chieftain: "You're being noisy. Be a bit quieter."

Banka: "Shut it. I'm just here to kill the miscreant for the sake of our
village."
Krun: "Kill?"

Chieftain: "That won't do. This person was guided by Kusechirei-sama. We
need to ascertain what kind of guidance brought him here."
Umi: "Banka. You're loud."

Banka: "Umi! Don't you talk back to your future husband! Hey old man! I
can't allow this! As the one who will become the next chieftain, I need to
set an example for everyone!"

Chieftain: "It's not yet decided that you will be the next chieftain. Watch
your words! And don't worry, we will have this person go to the Call Seed
Cave."
Umi: "Chieftain! That is...!"

Banka: "The Call Seed Cave! That's great! Do your best not to die!
Gahahaha!"
Umi: "*sigh*..."

Chieftain: "My apologies for this. He's my son, but he lacks manners. He's
quite a handful."
Krun: "No, what is this Call Seed Cave you mentioned?"

Chieftain: "Ah, right. You've been in this village for a month now. During
that time, Umi and the villagers have taken great care of you."
Krun: "Yes, indeed they have."
Chieftain: "So then! To repay that kindness, would you do us a favor?"
Krun: "Yes. If it's something I can do, anything at all."

Chieftain: "Well said. Then, I'd like you to go to this Call Seed Cave and
retrieve the ceremonial jewel located deep within."
Krun: "I see, understood. And this cave is a dangerous place..."
Chieftain: "That's right. And Umi, you will accompany him."
Umi: "Umi will go!"

Chieftain: "Yes. This must be some sort of fate. Go together and help each
other out."
Krun: "No, if it's such a dangerous place, I should go alone..."

Chieftain: "No! This is an order from the chieftain. Overcome the
difficulties together."
Umi: "Chieftain... I hate you. Banka's father."

Chieftain: "Uuuu. Don't say such things, Umi-chan! It's hard on the
chieftain too, but it's necessary for the sake of the village!"
Umi: "Hey, let's go home."
Krun: "Yeah..."
Chieftain: "Hohhohhoh, I'm counting on you."
Chieftain: "Hohoho, it seems to have gone well..."
Kru: "Yes, thanks to Umi, we were able to return safely."
Umi: "Umi did her best..."
Chieftain: "And... was there a guardian?"
Kru: "Yes... they were furious."
Chieftain: "I see... Did they say anything?"

Kru: "Yes. They said that we are not from the Kuseshi tribe and that we
came to steal the child of Kuseshi Rei."
Chieftain: "I see, good work."

Kru: "I'm sorry, it's my fault for going as an outsider, I unnecessarily
angered them."
Chieftain: "No worries. More importantly, we are planning a feast tonight."
Umi: "A feast! Meat!"

Chieftain: "That's right. Could you go hunting for the meat we'll use for
the feast?"
Umi: "Chieftain... Are you still going to make us work?"

Chieftain: "But, but Umi-chan! Since Banka is not around, we have no young
people to go hunting."
Kru: "Well, well. I'll go."
Umi: "Muu... Umi hates the Chieftain..."

Chieftain: "Umi-chan! But this guy smells like a good hunter, so I'm sure
he'll bring back a fine catch!"
Umi: "You... are you good at hunting?"
Kru: "Oh... well... I'm good at it, I guess..."
Kru: (I've actually never done it before...)
Umi: "Then it's fine. Let's go catch some meat quickly."
Chieftain: "I'm counting on you-"
Chieftain: "I'm expecting good prey."

Chieftain: "Oh, you're back. You've brought back quite a lot of pigs,
haven't you?"
Kru: "Yes, Umi was really enthusiastic..."
Chieftain: "Is that so... It's rare to see her so eager... *sniffle*..."
Kru: "Chieftain! What's wrong? Why are you suddenly crying?!"

Chieftain: "It's nothing... As one gets older, they become more tearful.
That girl has had a difficult past."
Kru: "She doesn't have her parents, after all."

Chieftain: "That's right... But perhaps it's thanks to you. She's become so
much more expressive."
Kru: "No, I haven't done anything."

Chieftain: "No, I can tell! Things are going in a good direction for her.
Let me thank you again... Thank you."

Kru: "No, please don't. I should be the one thanking you for all the care
I've received..."

Chieftain: "However, once your wounds are healed, you'll return to the
kingdom, won't you?"
Kru: "Ah... Yes. I suppose that's true."
Chieftain: "Umi will surely miss you."
Kru: "No, I don't think..."

Chieftain: "Oh! What's this delightful smell? The meal must be ready! Come
on, let's eat."
Kru: "Yes, I'll go now."
Chieftain: "Ah, you've arrived."
Kru: "Chieftain! What on earth is this...?"
Chieftain: "Hmm... I will explain. Could you come with Umi?"
Kru: "Understood. I'll bring her."

Umi: "Chieftain... Mi-A is... and the villagers too... What should Umi
do...?"

Chieftain: "Hmm... It's a plague that is said to occur once every few
decades in this region. It's my first encounter with it, but I have heard
from my predecessor how to deal with it."
Kru: "Then it can be cured, right?!"

Chieftain: "I can't assure you of safety, but it's not like there's no way
to deal with it. This disease is called Honyarara, and it is said that a
medicine made from a herb called Honyarara is effective against the
illness."
Kru: "Then we just need to gather that herb, right?!"

Chieftain: "That's right... However, the herb grows on the summit of a very
high mountain called Honyarara Mountain. We must go there to collect it."
Kru: "I'll go! I'll leave right away."

Chieftain: "Thank you. But that mountain is a bit far, and the monsters
living there are incomparably stronger than the ones around here. It's too
much for you to go alone... So, Umi..."
Umi: "Eh...?"
Chieftain: "Would you accompany Kru to that mountain?"

Kru: "Umi... I know you're worried about Mi-A, but if we go quickly and
make the medicine, she'll surely get better!"
Umi: "...I... I can't..."

Chieftain: "Umi, I understand that I'm asking you to do something
difficult. But right now, you and Kru are the only ones who can move in
this village..."
Umi: "Umi... is scared..."
Kru: "Umi!"
Chieftain: "It seems impossible after all..."
Kru: "Chieftain! Is there a reason for this?"

Chieftain: "Hmm... Umi has never left this forest... You know that her
parents are deceased, right?"
Kru: "Yes, I'm aware."

Chieftain: "Her mother fell ill and passed away shortly after giving birth
to Umi... She had a weak constitution..."

Chieftain: "Umi has been terribly hard on herself. She's been regretting
her decision to leave the forest on her own, and it left her unable to
speak for about three years..."
Kru: "Such a thing happened..."

Chieftain: "Since then, Umi has been unable to leave this forest... I
wanted to do something to help her, but there was nothing I could do..."

Kru: "(I see... So that's why she said she couldn't go see the ocean that
time...)"
Chieftain: "So, you there... Could you guide Umi?"
Kru: "Eh? Me?"

Chieftain: "Yes, you... I've known Umi since she was a child. That Umi, who
doesn't open her heart to others, truly smiles from her heart when she's
with you."

Chieftain: "I'm sure you can lead Umi in the right direction... I'm
counting on you."
Kru: "...I don't know if I can do it, but... I'll try!!"
Chieftain: "Oh! Have you guys returned⁉ Did you find the Nani Nani⁉"
Kru: "Yes. Is this okay?"

Chieftain: "Ah, exactly this! You've done well! Now, let's get to making
the medicine right away!"

The chieftain and Kru's group immediately made the medicine and distributed
it to the villagers.

The medicine was potent, and the villagers began to recover one after
another.

Chieftain: "Regarding the recent turmoil... As the chieftain, I take it
very seriously. I wonder if it's truly for the best to keep our village
entrance closed and cut off all contact with the outside world..."

Villager A: "I see... Indeed, we must consider the risks of isolating
ourselves."
バンカ2

Banka: "I'm against it! We've managed up until now, haven't we? We'll
figure something out from here on too!"
Villager B: "But, if it weren't for Kru-san..."
バンカ3

Banka: "Shut up! Don't rely on outsiders! And I don't like that this guy is
even part of this meeting in the first place!"

Chieftain: "Now, Banka. Don't get emotional. And Kru, could we hear your
opinion as well?"

Kru: "Well, if I may be so bold to offer my opinion... I believe there's a
limit to dealing with emergencies like this on our own..."
バンカ2
Banka: "What did you say!"
Chieftain: "Now, Banka, no need to get excited."
Villager B: "Banka-san, please calm down a bit."
バンカ7
Banka: "Grr..."

Kru: "Ahem, let me continue. This time it was a disease, but there could be
various other things. Earthquakes, typhoons, famine, epidemics, a surge in
monster populations..."
Chieftain: "That's true."

Kru: "Yes. This time, fortunately, an adult man like myself was able to
act. But what if only children or women were able to move? Please imagine
that scenario based on this case."

Villager A: "Certainly, my child couldn't climb to the top of that mountain
to gather herbs."
Villager C: "Right. My wife couldn't do it either."

Kru: "But what about this? If we make our way through the forest to call
for help from the kingdom. Or if we set up something like a trading post
nearby, we could deal with it just by sending a message there, couldn't
we?"
Chieftain: "I see. That certainly sounds realistic."
バンカ3

Banka: "We don't need that kind of thing! We don't need to borrow the
strength of outsiders! I'm going to be the next chieftain! My policy should
naturally become the village's policy!"

Chieftain: "Banka. If you claim to be the next chieftain, what were you
doing during this turmoil?"
バンカ6
Banka: "I... I was..."

Chieftain: "You left the village and went off to some pleasure district,
didn't you?"
バンカ3
Banka: "Wha! I didn't do anything like that!"
Villager A: "Banka-san... Everyone knows."
Villager C: "Did you think you hadn't been found out?"

Villager D: "And you talk about being the next chieftain? Don't you think
that's a bit far-fetched?"
バンカ6
Banka: "You guys..."

Chieftain: "Banka. I won't blame you for breaking the village's taboo and
indulging yourself outside this time. However, to speak so lightly of
becoming the next chieftain after such behavior during a crisis... How many
villagers do you think you've put in danger?"
バンカ3
Banka: "Father!"

Chieftain: "Moreover, it was Kru, the outsider you speak of, who settled
this turmoil. That fact is undeniable."
バンカ2

Banka: "Hmph! Even if you all say so, I won't accept it! If it comes to a
fight, I'm stronger! Hey you! Let's have a match!"
Kru: "Eh, right now?"
バンカ3
Banka: "Yes! What's wrong? Are you scared to fight me?"
Kru: "No, that's not quite it, but it's true that I don't want to fight."
バンカ8

Banka: "Hmph! See what I mean! He's chickening out. Someone who can't fight
here can't be the next chieftain! It's clear that I'm stronger and more
suitable to be chieftain than he is, so I'm out of here!"
Chieftain: "Wait, Banka!"
Biku!
バンカ6
Banka: "What... Father..."
Chieftain: "Sigh... Banka. I will grant your wish..."
バンカ1
Banka: "Really, Father?! Then I'll be the next chieftain!"
Chieftain: "I'm begging you, Kru... please fight Banka..."
Kru: "Chieftain..."
Villager A: "Chieftain... that's..."
Villager B: "You should probably refrain from doing that..."
Chieftain: "It's fine... It's necessary to face reality..."
バンカ6
Banka: "Father! That's... that is..."
Chieftain: "I'm counting on you, Kru... as you see..."
Kru: "Chieftain... please raise your head. I understand..."
Chieftain: "Oh... Kru... I am in your debt."
バンカ3
Banka: "What! You..."

Chieftain: "Banka... I will grant your wish and let you fight... Now, show
us this strength you speak of. Kru... I'm counting on you..."
Kru: "Yes."
Kru: (But even so...)
Chieftain: "Then let's begin!"
バンカ6

Banka: "You! You! You're going to regret this! If you want to back out,
now's your chance!"
Kru: "Ah... right..."
Kru: (This is bad... I might seriously injure him... In this case...)
Glare!
バンカ9
Banka: "Eek!"
Bubbling...
Thud!
Villager A: "You've got to be kidding..."
Villager B: "Just with fighting spirit..."
Chieftain: "Sigh... pathetic... Everyone, please help carry Banka..."
Chieftain: "Sigh. I'm sorry, Kru. I apologize on behalf of my son."

Kru: "No, please don't worry about it. I can understand his turbulent
feelings."

Chieftain: "I'm relieved. Let's continue the meeting. Kru, there's
something important I need to ask of you."
Kru: "Yes?"

Chieftain: "I want you to be the bridge between the kingdom and our
village. I wish to explore a path where we can coexist as good neighbors."
Villager A: "Chieftain!"
Villager C: "That goes against the teachings of Lord Xesirei!"

Chieftain: "Calm down... My respect for Lord Xesirei remains unchanged, but
it's equally important to create a future where our children can live in
peace."
Villager D: "Chieftain..."
Chieftain: "Kru... what do you think? I'd like to hear your opinion."

Kru: "Well, I think it would be very good for the village. Not only will
people come and go, but the exchange of goods will also become more active,
leading to a richer life."
Villager B: "Oh..."

Kru: "However... this is just speculation on my part, but I don't think the
upper echelons of the kingdom are likely to adopt a friendly policy."
Chieftain: "Oh? And why is that?"

Kru: "That's because Chancellor Shif holds a noble-centric view... in a
word, he's discriminatory. Especially towards commoners and multiple
races."

Chieftain: "I see... Our village may not be very flexible in its thinking
either... perhaps it's the same everywhere."

Kru: "Yes... However, I believe that the kingdom will surely gain some
benefits from trading with this village. It's worth trying to negotiate."

Chieftain: "That's right. If we can't come to an understanding after trying
to negotiate, then we can think about what to do next. So, Kru, can you go
to the kingdom and make an effort to set up a negotiation?"
Kru: "Yes!"

Chieftain: "Thank you. Then, I'll appoint Umi as the envoy from our
village. The two of you, please work together to negotiate."
Kru: "Umi as an envoy?"
Villager A: "Chieftain, isn't that a bit too much of a burden...?"

Chieftain: "As you all know, Umi is going to become a priestess. She's
going to be a very important figure for this village, so it would be good
for her to start her duties and gain experience from now."

Kru: "That girl is going to be a priestess? Can she really handle such an
important role...?"

Chieftain: "It'll be fine. Rather, it's something that has been decided, so
we have no choice but to make it work. Now, Kru! Head to the kingdom with
Umi!"
Kru: "Understood! I'll be on my way."
hideHpGauge
Chieftain: "Well... this has turned into quite the predicament..."
Villager A: "Chieftain! Why did the barrier break?"
Villager B: "It must be because Kru and the others headed to the kingdom."

Chieftain: "No, that seems unlikely... It would mean Umi taught them the
teleportation spell..."
Umi: "Umi didn't do such a thing!"

Chieftain: "Ah, I know. It's probably the doing of my foolish son who isn't
here."
Villager C: "Banka did it!"
Villager D: "Why would he do such a thing!"

Chieftain: "I don't know the reason. Either he was being wasteful and got
kidnapped, or he lured them himself... In any case, it's most likely that
the leak came from there."
Villager A: "Damn it! He's hopeless!"

Kru: "Let's calm down. For now, let's put Banka aside and think about what
to do next."
Villager A: "You're right."
Villager B: "Yeah, let's think about what to do."
Chieftain: "So the main culprit this time is still..."
Kru: "Yes, I believe it's Chancellor Shif's doing."
Umi: "That scumbag."

Kru: "Shif was after the altar of Lord Kuseshirei. And he was after Umi as
well."

Chieftain: "I see... Whatever he plans to do with it, it's certain that we
are in danger."

Kru: "Yes. Fortunately, there have been no fatalities this time, but
learning from this failure, they might come with an even larger force next
time."
Umi: "They're coming again?"
Kru: "Yes. Probably an unimaginable horde will descend upon us."
Chieftain: "This is troubling..."
Kru: "Chieftain. Is it not possible to change the barrier spell?"

Chieftain: "Ah. I was considering that as well. It's probably the most
realistic solution."
Villager C: "There was such a method!"
Villager D: "Then let's get to it quickly!"

Chieftain: "That's right... However, there's a difficulty. We can make
changes to the barrier, but it requires the caster to continue casting the
spell for an entire day."
Kru: "An entire day?!"

Chieftain: "That's right. And during that time, they cannot move a single
step away from the stone tablet."
Kru: "I see... That's troublesome."
Villager A: "What's so troublesome about it?"

Kru: "Well. We'll have to meet the enemy outside the barrier and ensure not
a single one of them gets through."
Chieftain: "Exactly. Whether our village has the strength to do that..."
Villager A: "Let's all fight together!"
Villager B: "Yes! We'll protect this village!"
Chieftain: "That's right... We have no other choice but to do it."
Kru: "That's right, Chieftain. We'll manage somehow."

Chieftain: "No, Kru. This time I cannot rely on you. You are not one of our
villagers, and I cannot ask you to risk your life in battle."
Villager C: "But..."
Villager D: "If Kru isn't here..."
Umi: "Kru..."

Kru: "It's alright, Umi. Chieftain... I really like this village. And
everyone in it..."
Chieftain: "Kru..."
Kru: "So please, let me stake my life for this village!"
Villager A: "Mr. Kru..."
Villager B: "You... you're a real man!"
Villager C: "Thank you... thank you so much..."
Chieftain: "Are you really sure about this?"

Kru: "Chieftain! A man doesn't go back on his word! Besides, it's too late
for formalities! Haven't you been working me to the bone already?"
Umi: "That's really true."
Chieftain: "Ho ho ho. That's a sharp one, it hurts my ears."
Kru: "Well then"

Chieftain: "I'm counting on you... Kru... I am truly grateful from the
bottom of my heart."
Villager A: "Mr. Kru... thank you."
Villager D: "It's really good that you fell into the river."

Chieftain: "I truly wish you were my son. Win or lose... I will be proud of
you."
Kru: "Don't be so dramatic! Now, let's get started with the work!"
